1. The Q-Train Offline Download (Text-Only Mode)

The under-river tunnels connecting Manhattan and Brooklyn are notoriously weak cellular zones. To make text instantly 
available between Canal and DeKalb, your application needs an Offline-First Storage Engine:

React Implementation: Use a browser Service Worker combined with IndexedDB (via a library like Dexie.js).

The Workflow: When the user is above ground, React fires a fetch request to your PHP backend. Your backend 
returns a compressed, text-only JSON payload of the day’s articles. React dumps this text directly into IndexedDB.

The Result: When the train drops underground and loses connection, the React app detects the offline state 
(navigator.onLine === false) and seamlessly pulls the raw text straight from local device storage.





